SIMPLE: glazer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glazer
<hw>Glaz"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
applies glazing, as in pottery manufacture, etc.; one who gives a
glasslike or glossy surface to anything; a calenderer or smoother of
cloth, paper, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tool or machine used in glazing, polishing,
smoothing, etc.; amoung cutlers and lapidaries, a wooden wheel covered
with emery, or having a band of lead and tin alloy, for polishing
cutlery, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glazier</ent>⟦br⟧
